Program: Great Lives
Title: Liza Tarbuck on Nikola Tesla
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09nvrs5
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 23 Jan 2018
Actor and broadcaster Liza Tarbuck chooses the extraordinary life of the Serbian-American scientist Nikola Tesla whose inventions were ahead of his time. He founded the Tesla Electric Light Company and was responsible for the introduction of the AC current in America, seeing off competition from his rival and former hero Thomas Edison. The fortunes and misfortunes of this brilliant and eccentric man who died virtually penniless in a New York hotel room are discussed by Liza and Matthew with the help of Professor Iwan Morus from Aberystwyth University. Producer: Maggie Ayre. Show less